  1. What does the stroke aesthetic do? What shapes does it work with? (Hint: use?geom_point) Try it with shape=21 and stroke=displ in your code from 3.3.1.1.
vignette("ggplot2-specs")
#this functions helps us to know more about ggplot2 specs such as stroke,lines and etc
ggplot(data=mpg)+
 geom_point(mapping = aes(x= fl,y= hwy,stroke= displ),shape= 21)

#other ways to use stroke

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x= fl,y= cty,stroke= displ), stroke = 4, shape = 0) 

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x= hwy,y= fl,stroke= displ), stroke = 3)

#The thickness of the stroke can be set it helps changing thickness of the borders of a shape if assigned (if you use non-filled shapes). This aesthetic's definition refers to a numerical number, which typically falls between 1 and 5 and the thickness is adjusted according to the numerical value given
#here we have given stroke to a continous variable and we have given shape as 21 so the scatter plot is plotted with the 21 shape and the thickness is decided according to the displ value.
